  "body": " When we are issuing a request to apiserver from client, this is being throttled according to client-specific throttler:\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/client/restclient/request.go#L854\n\nHowever, if we get 429 error from apiserver, the retry of it is not being throttled:\nhttps://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/client/restclient/request.go#L798\n\nThis means, if apiserver is overloaded and is returning 429, the client may potentially send a lot more requests (that are retires) than it actually can according to its QPS limits. This may lead to overloaded apiserver even more...\n\nThe fix is it try throttle the request that is retried as a result of 429 received previously.\n\n@kubernetes/sig-api-machinery @lavalamp @gmarek @kubernetes/sig-scalability \n",
